  "body": "When I want to call a method of contract, which would do a write operation, I would send a transaction, which would contain the arguments of method. These arguments would be encoded or hash (using SHA3?) to a HEX string. Then this HEX string will be signed by my private key using ECDSA. Finally a final string will be put in the input field of transaction object. \r\n\r\nIs my understanding correct? If right, as hash process could not be reversed, how could I get the real arguments from transaction?",
