    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "Transaction payloads are encoded using the ABI spec. Basically the first [4 bytes](https://github.com/ethereum/wiki/wiki/Ethereum-Contract-ABI#function-selector) indicate which function of the contract should be invoked. The remaining bytes are the [arguments](https://github.com/ethereum/wiki/wiki/Ethereum-Contract-ABI#argument-encoding).\r\n\r\nTo properly decode transaction data you need to have the contract ABI. Web3 has support the ABI spec, not sure if this is exposed in its API. If you want to use go you can take a look at the `github.com/ethereum/go-ethereum/accounts/abi` package.\r\n\r\nAlso note, users can put whatever they want in the payload. It doesn't have to a valid payload nor does the target has to be a contract.",
